{"key":"processedPost-11520730","value":{"id":11520730,"first":11520011,"last":11520730,"when":1259110076,"utime":"11/25/09 02:47 AM","content":"In my experience, recovery is slightly faster and performance slightly better in tray culture when the grains are layered into the substrate rather than mixed.&nbsp; However, the gain is minor, and many growers mix the spawn with the substrate and have great success.<br /><br />With substrate bags, I've found they colonize sooner when tied shut and shaken.&nbsp; This may be because the grains which end up on top of the substrate don't dry out and are not as susceptible to contamination as grains left exposed on an open tray.<br />RR","title":"Re: Poll: layer or mix, spawn and sub"}}